  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf.\u0bb5\u0bbf.\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc7\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The result may change - Tamil People's National Alliance President CV Wigneswaran",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "On Tuesday 19th, I handed over a letter containing 6 demands on behalf of the Tamil people to the President and the new presidential candidate, Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "Wigneswaran MP said his decision to remain neutral may change at times. He said.",
        "Presidential candidates such as Ranil Wickramasinghe, Dallas Alagapperuma and Anurakumara Dissanayake are involved in efforts to seek the support of the parties as the vote to elect the new President is to be held in Parliament at 10 am on Wednesday.",
        "In this case, the president of the Tamil People's National Alliance and Member of Parliament, Justice C.V. He said this when he was asked whether there were any changes in the decision of your middle position as the main opposition leader Sajith Premadasa withdrew from the race for the presidential post as already stated by Wigneswaran.",
        "We have handed over a letter containing 6 demands on behalf of the Tamil people to the replying president and the new presidential candidate, Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "He gave some assurances in this regard. However, I will take the final decision only after discussing with my partner parties and other Tamil party leaders. Then in some jobs the decision may change in the middle of the situation.",
        "Meanwhile, none of the other presidential candidates sought the support of my party. But it was Ranil Wickremesinghe who directly sought my support.",
        "That is why I personally handed him a letter containing 6 demands on behalf of the Tamil people. He immediately read it and gave some assurances. I was also going to hand over this letter to the Leader of the Opposition, Sajith Premadasa. But he said he did not hand him over as he withdrew from the race for the presidency at the last moment."
      ],
